# Tagging Rules (This Vault)

Use tags to provide architecture, not content. Follow Category/Detail format, all lowercase.

## Required
- Add at least one `#type/*` tag
- Add one or more `#theme/*` tags

## Recommended
- Add `#target/*` when a specific purpose exists
- Add `#structure/*` for structure notes (MOC, index, etc.)
- Add focused `#keyword/*` tags (technical concepts)
- Keep total tags around 5–7; avoid over-tagging

## Format
- Lowercase; use `category/detail`
- Place tags at the bottom of the note body (not YAML) unless the user asks otherwise
- Do not invent new top-level categories without user approval

## Allowed Categories (with examples)
- Type: `#type/fleeting`, `#type/literature`, `#type/permanent`, `#type/project`, `#type/structure`, `#type/note`, `#type/sketchnote`, `#type/book`, `#type/quote`, `#type/term`, `#type/person`, `#type/tool`, `#type/meeting`, `#type/post`, `#type/question`, `#type/prompt`, `#type/recipe`, `#type/okr`, `#type/rule`, `#type/example`, `#type/dataview`
- Structure: `#structure/moc`, `#structure/index`, `#structure/about`, `#structure/canvas`, `#structure/list`
- Theme: `#theme/zettelkasten`, `#theme/productivity`, `#theme/learning`, `#theme/research`, `#theme/pkm`, `#theme/sketchnotes`, `#theme/writing`, `#theme/thinking`, `#theme/datastory`, `#theme/cooking`, `#theme/finance`, `#theme/objectives`
- Target: `#target/starterkit`, `#target/project`, `#target/github`, `#target/linkedin`, `#target/forumzettelkasten`, `#target/forumobsidian`, `#target/reddit`
- Role: `#role/author`, `#role/expert`, `#role/visualthinker`, `#role/networkedthinker`
- Status: `#status/open`, `#status/wip`, `#status/backlog`, `#status/active`
